As of Tuesday, veteran US diplomat Ronald Spiers will be the new undersecretary- general for General Assembly affairs, the top-ranking American post at the UN.
His  nomination had been an open secret for months.
He replaces Joseph Verner Reed.
Spiers,  64, has served at the US embassy in London and has been ambassador to the Bahamas,  Turkey, and Pakistan.
He has been a member of the US delegation to the UN and director  of political affairs for the US Arms Control and Disarmament Agency.
At the State  Department, he was director of NATO Affairs, assistant secretary in charge of Political- Military Affairs, director of Intelligence and Research, and undersecretary for  management. 
